<title type="html"><![CDATA[Emulating NOAC based plug-n-play games]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1792&amp;p=15214#p15214"><![CDATA[
This might sound like a really bad idea at first, but since many of these plug-n-play game systems are based on NOACs, shouldn't it be possible to add support for the games to a NES emulator via new mappers.  That is, simply treat the games as if they were any other pirate multicart.  I realize that NOACs are slightly different than a real NES, but then again, emulators support some multi-carts that come packed with Famiclones.<br /><br />Commercial dev for the NES never stopped, if you consider NOAC dev to be NES dev.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=94">Jagasian</a> — Sat Jul 08, 2006 8:07 am</p><hr />
